apartments that accept pets student housing search search this site stanford university student housing housing options apply for housing moving in moving out living in housing calendar home community housing apartments that accept pets be aware that very few places will allow pets especially dogs those that do accept pets may require an additional pet deposit or monthly pet rent one thing that you can do to increase the likelihood of finding a place to live with your pet is to obtain written references from past landlords this will help prospective landlords feel safe in renting to you and your pet you should also check the humane society of silicon valley web site it has tips for finding pet friendly housing listed below are some apartment complexes that accept pets they may or may not have current vacancies cats and dogs arbor terrace 555 east el camino real sunnyvale 408 738 0935 dogs must be 20 pounds or less avalon at creekside 151 calderon mountain view 650 968 8351 dogs must be 60 pounds or less and 25 or less maximum of 2 pets the cascades 870 east el camino real sunnyvale 408 730 2500 dogs must be 20 pounds or less curtner square 250 curtner street palo alto 650 493 8670 cats and small dogs only pet references required depends on pet fremont properties properties in menlo park mountain view palo alto and sunnyvale 650 851 5650 no puppies only certain dog breeds allowed cats welcome highland gardens apartments 234 esceula avenue mountain view 650 964 3494 breed restrictions for dogs 2 pets maximum palo alto park 2586 w bayshore palo alto 650 856 0633 no puppies 20 lb limit additional $500 pet deposit required park place south apartments 800 high school way mountain view 650 961 6500 2 pets max 40 pound limit breed restrictions on dogs pet deposit monthly pet rent sharon apartments 2050 california street mountain view 650 966 8647 pets up to 15 pounds allowed with an extra $100 pet deposit sierra vista apartments 917 sierra vista avenue mountain view 408 745